SIMPLE: swish
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swish
<hw>Swish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[From the sound. Cf.
<er>Swash</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To flourish, so as to make the
sound <xex>swish</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To flog; to lash.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swish
<hw>Swish</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To dash; to swash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Swish
<hw>Swish</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sound of quick
movement, as of something whirled through the air.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Light driven spray.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swiss</ent>⟦br⟧
